{
  "stem": "5758.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Bretholz, ?] with whom I am still today, at least we see each other once a year, or we write to each other once a month.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We are very close.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He lives in Baltimore.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Anyhow, we went-- he also got an affidavit to go to America.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in 1947, we both went on the same boat, [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Leo Bretholz ?] and myself.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Went to America.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I went to New York because my oldest brother lived in New York.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he went to his aunt.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He had an aunt in Baltimore, Maryland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I worked for a year in New York, learning English at night classes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Then I was a packer in some firm.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Then my friend Leo told me to join him in Baltimore, Maryland, and he has a job for me in the same firm where he works, in a textile firm.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So I was quite happy to go to Baltimore.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we, again, had our apartment together, and lived there with Leo.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] it's a-- it's a-- it was a joy, really, to be together with a big group of people.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To make a long story short, really, it is-- life started to get normal again.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Suddenly, somebody comes to me and said, hey, do you want to meet somebody from the old country?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, sure, I don't mind meeting somebody from the old country.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because in America, every Saturday you had to have a date.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You had to have a date.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I phoned up my-- she gave me a phone number.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She said, phone up that girl from the old country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[SIGHS] This is how I make a date over the telephone with somebody called Freda Bloom.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we spoke for one hour on the telephone.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
